{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"31e","heading":"Geologic mapping program 5-year plan","label":"31e Geologic mapping program 5-year plan","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s31e","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t43/ch2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft43%2Fs31e","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","Prior ProvisionsA prior section 31e, , , ; , , , provided for the preparation of a geologic mapping program implementation plan, prior to repeal by , , .Pub. L. 102–285, § 6106 Stat. 170Pub. L. 105–36, § 3(d)111 Stat. 1110Pub. L. 106–148, § 6113 Stat. 1722May 18, 1992Aug. 5, 1997Dec. 9, 1999"],"amendments":["Prior ProvisionsA prior section 31e, , , ; , , , provided for the preparation of a geologic mapping program implementation plan, prior to repeal by , , .Pub. L. 102–285, § 6106 Stat. 170Pub. L. 105–36, § 3(d)111 Stat. 1110Pub. L. 106–148, § 6113 Stat. 1722May 18, 1992Aug. 5, 1997Dec. 9, 1999"],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":"In general","label":"a In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s31e/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t43/s31e","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft43%2Fs31e%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Secretary, acting through the Director, shall, with the advice and review of the advisory committee, prepare a 5-year plan for the geologic mapping program.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":"Requirements","label":"b Requirements","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s31e/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t43/s31e","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft43%2Fs31e%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s31e/b/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t43/s31e/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft43%2Fs31e%2Fb%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"overall priorities for the geologic mapping program; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s31e/b/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t43/s31e/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft43%2Fs31e%2Fb%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s31e/b/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t43/s31e/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft43%2Fs31e%2Fb%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the role of the Survey in the capacity of overall management lead, including the responsibility for developing the national geologic mapping program that meets Federal needs while fostering State needs;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s31e/b/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t43/s31e/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft43%2Fs31e%2Fb%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the responsibilities of the State geological surveys, with emphasis on mechanisms that incorporate the needs, missions, capabilities, and requirements of the State geological surveys, into the nationwide geologic mapping program;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s31e/b/2/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t43/s31e/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft43%2Fs31e%2Fb%2F2%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s31e/b/2/C/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t43/s31e/b/2/C","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft43%2Fs31e%2Fb%2F2%2FC%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subclause","nativeType":"subclause","number":"I","heading":null,"label":"I","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s31e/b/2/C/i/I","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t43/s31e/b/2/C/i","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft43%2Fs31e%2Fb%2F2%2FC%2Fi%2FI","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Federal mission requirements for geologic map information;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subclause","nativeType":"subclause","number":"II","heading":null,"label":"II","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s31e/b/2/C/i/II","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t43/s31e/b/2/C/i","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft43%2Fs31e%2Fb%2F2%2FC%2Fi%2FII","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"critical scientific problems that require geologic maps for their resolution; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subclause","nativeType":"subclause","number":"III","heading":null,"label":"III","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s31e/b/2/C/i/III","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t43/s31e/b/2/C/i","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft43%2Fs31e%2Fb%2F2%2FC%2Fi%2FIII","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"shared Federal and State needs for geologic maps, in which joint Federal-State geologic mapping projects are in the national interest;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s31e/b/2/C/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t43/s31e/b/2/C","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft43%2Fs31e%2Fb%2F2%2FC%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subclause","nativeType":"subclause","number":"I","heading":null,"label":"I","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s31e/b/2/C/ii/I","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t43/s31e/b/2/C/ii","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft43%2Fs31e%2Fb%2F2%2FC%2Fii%2FI","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"specific intrastate needs for geologic map information; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subclause","nativeType":"subclause","number":"II","heading":null,"label":"II","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s31e/b/2/C/ii/II","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t43/s31e/b/2/C/ii","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft43%2Fs31e%2Fb%2F2%2FC%2Fii%2FII","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"interstate needs shared by adjacent States that have common requirements; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"iii","heading":null,"label":"iii","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s31e/b/2/C/iii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t43/s31e/b/2/C","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft43%2Fs31e%2Fb%2F2%2FC%2Fiii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"for the education component, a priority-setting mechanism that responds to requirements for geologic map information that are dictated by Federal and State mission requirements;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"D","heading":null,"label":"D","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s31e/b/2/D","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t43/s31e/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft43%2Fs31e%2Fb%2F2%2FD","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":nu